    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <p>
        <em><xar:mlstring>Lists is a module that can hold lists of items.</xar:mlstring></em>
        <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing the following tasks:</xar:mlstring>
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Allow for the input of user defined lists of items.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Interact with the surveys module.</xar:mlstring></li>

    </ol>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <p>
        <xar:mlstring>This module is packed with two example lists: one of countries, and another one of years.</xar:mlstring>
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Install the lists module.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Make sure the Dynamic Data module is present.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Go to the admin area of Dynamic Data</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Go to import</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Refresh the directory for modules/lists</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Import the list types data with the option "preserve item ids"</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Import the list items data.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring> Locate the lists in the lists module.</xar:mlstring></li>
    </ol>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></h3>
